snippet.textDisplay: I'm not going to complain. I was kinda let down with the Last Jedi due to expectations. But this movie really apologized for that. snippet.textDisplay: The Scene were Han Appears to Kylo….So this was not Han the force ghost; because we all know that could never have happened for obvious reasons. Leia performed the same Jedi act that Luke did in the last Jedi. Once she accomplished what she set out to do, which was ultimately turn Kylo back to the light, she was still a guiding force until all was complete and she become one with the force. This movie is good enough to be seen a few more times, just to get a much more clearer understanding of everything that happened in it. But yes Han was not a force ghost but was Leia appearing to her son as his father in the last image that he remembered him. Love the channel!!!

When Han appeared he was not a force ghost, force ghosts glow. He was a manifestation of Kylo's memories and guilty conscious because there was still good in him from a jedi perspective, or conflict in him from a darkside perspective, tht's way more dangerous then any force ghost.


Rey grew up without parents around, as a scavenger growing up she had to fight off other scavengers just to eat and to survive from a very young age, so she already knew how to fight at least with her staff and hand to hand combat while Luke for example grew up sheltered as a moisture farmer he didn't even hold a blaster before leaving his home planet, also when supposedly snoke linked Rey and Kylo's minds they could see and feel each others past and future experiences so part of his training also became hers.


Yeah i agree Palpatine died a little to quick (or did he!? lol).


She buried the lightsabers on tht spot because i think she's going to start a new Jedi temple on tht spot so it's holy ground or sand. It's the spot were the force impregnated Shmi, and were Anakin was conceived. Not to far away from where unknowingly Vader 1st appeared later on.
